items.title: Lululemon shares drop 15% as CEO says inflation, economic concerns are weighing on spending
items.description: Lululemon beat on earnings but disappointed with its 2025 guidance in its fourth-quarter earnings report.

items.title: Nike expects sales will plunge in current quarter as it faces tariffs, sliding consumer confidence
items.description: Nike is trying to execute a turnaround under new CEO Elliott Hill.

items.title: Micron shares jump on earnings beat, rosy guidance as data center revenue triples
items.description: Micron shares rose in extended trading Thursday after the company reported better-than-expected results and issued guidance that topped estimates.

items.title: Darden Restaurants sales disappoint, but Olive Garden parent sees consumers continuing to spend
items.description: Olive Garden and LongHorn Steakhouse reported weaker-than-expected same-store sales growth in Darden's latest quarter.

items.title: Tencent profit surges 90% as it touts AI revenue boost and ramps up spending
items.description: Tencent on Wednesday posted a fourth-quarter beat on top and bottom line driven by a surge in gaming and advertising revenue.
